pslog single-header distribution
Version: @PSLOG_VERSION@
Artifact: @PSLOG_SINGLE_HEADER_FILENAME@

This file is a generated distribution artifact. The multi-file source tree is
the implementation source of truth. Do not edit this file directly inside the
repository.

Quick start

  Normal include mode:

    #include "@PSLOG_SINGLE_HEADER_FILENAME@"

  Implementation mode:

    #define PSLOG_IMPLEMENTATION
    #include "@PSLOG_SINGLE_HEADER_FILENAME@"

  Define PSLOG_IMPLEMENTATION in exactly one C translation unit in your
  program. Other translation units should include the header without defining
  PSLOG_IMPLEMENTATION.

Configuration notes

  - This single-header distribution targets the same pthread-backed platforms
    as the normal library build.
  - The generated header contains the public API first and the implementation
    under the PSLOG_IMPLEMENTATION section.
  - The normal packaged library, tests, and examples remain the correctness
    source of truth. This distribution artifact is generated from that source.

